H0.text: Gametophytes are the structures that female spores develop into inside female cones.

H1.text: Gymnosperms are the female plants that develop from female spores inside female cones.

H2.text: Filaments are the structures into which female spores develop inside female cones.

H3.text: Tubules are the structures into which female spores develop inside female cones.

A4.text: The female gametophyte in gymnosperms differs from the male gametophyte as it spends its whole life cycle in one organ, the ovule located inside the megastrobilus or female cone.

A5.text: The female gametophyte forms from a diploid megaspore that undergoes meiosis and starts being singled celled.
